ff", "coach_final_fours_diff", "coach_win_rate_diff", "ast_rate_diff", "seed_disagreement"], "method": "gradient-boosting gain on 2026 tournament games (normalized)", "narrative": {"headline": "What the 2026 tournament actually rewarded", "body": "Because Hindsight is trained on the 67 tournament games themselves, its importance chart is a read-out of the variables that separated this year's winners from losers. <strong>seed_disagreement</strong> tops the list \u2014 the gap between where the committee seeded a team and where their underlying efficiency said they belonged. In basketball terms: teams the bracket committee under-rated won games they were statistically supposed to win but were slotted as underdogs. <strong>wab_diff</strong> (Wins Above Bubble) and <strong>adj_em_diff</strong> round out the top three \u2014 r\u00e9sum\u00e9 depth and points-per-possession dominance."}, "comparison_models": {"Greg_v1": {"feature_cols": ["con_adj_oe_diff", "con_adj_de_diff", "adj_em_diff", "seed_diff", "wab_diff", "b_adj_em", "conf_winpct_diff", "sos_diff", "a_adj_em", "qual_games_diff", "adj_o_diff", "qual_barthag_diff", "is_late_round", "seed_product", "qual_o_diff", "coach_tourn_wins_diff", "adj_d_diff", "ncsos_diff", "a_adj_o", "seed_sum", "consos_diff", "b_adj_o", "qual_d_diff", "b_barthag", "coach_appearances_diff", "elite_sos_diff", "a_adj_d", "coach_final_fours_diff"], "importances": [{"feature": "sos_diff", "importance": 0.32225118097954597}, {"feature": "consos_diff", "importance": 0.15391287715456245}, {"feature": "qual_barthag_diff", "importance": 0.14088442443514687}, {"feature": "conf_winpct_diff", "importance": 0.14053395918273945}, {"feature": "ncsos_diff", "importance": 0.11464248428628555}, {"feature": "elite_sos_diff", "importance": 0.033424232597525}, {"feature": "is_late_round", "importance": 0.027838727721683786}, {"feature": "b_barthag", "importance": 0.015485332267234626}, {"feature": "con_adj_oe_diff", "importance": 0.007154490532979937}, {"feature": "con_adj_de_diff", "importance": 0.006656125520351773}, {"feature": "wab_diff", "importance": 0.006197066668483074}, {"feature": "adj_em_diff", "importance": 0.0058555726209956836}, {"feature": "qual_games_diff", "importance": 0.003579938417953188}, {"feature": "a_adj_em", "importance": 0.003227025963387045}, {"feature": "adj_d_diff", "importance": 0.003019953345797099}, {"feature": "seed_diff", "importance": 0.0029766640354898896}, {"feature": "adj_o_diff", "importance": 0.0028356192769663576}, {"feature": "b_adj_em", "importance": 0.002628546657307544}, {"feature": "a_adj_o", "importance": 0.0019730160501250553}, {"feature": "a_adj_d", "importance": 0.0012540099124868777}, {"feature": "seed_sum", "importance": 0.001015512125605971}, {"feature": "b_adj_o", "importance": 0.0008626032248433983}, {"feature": "coach_final_fours_diff", "importance": 0.000581674864611595}, {"feature": "qual_d_diff", "importance": 0.00038552227136835185}, {"feature": "seed_product", "importance": 0.00033602150916017527}, {"feature": "coach_tourn_wins_diff", "importance": 0.00022833120369081554}, {"feature": "qual_o_diff", "importance": 0.0002026401214400633}, {"feature": "coach_appearances_diff", "importance": 5.644705223247335e-05}], "method": "|\u03b2| from Ridge regression (normalized)", "narrative": {"headline": "Greg_v1 is a r\u00e9sum\u00e9 model", "body": "Greg_v1 spreads 28 features across a Ridge regression and leans hardest on <strong>strength-of-schedule</strong> signals \u2014 overall SOS, conference SOS, and how teams fared against top-Barthag opponents. Its basketball theory: tournaments reward teams forged by tough competition. Who you beat all winter matters more than how prettily you beat them. That worked well for this year (86.6% pick accuracy, Michigan as champion), but notice how little weight it placed on <strong>seed_disagreement</strong> \u2014 the one feature Hindsight says mattered most. Greg_v1 trusts the committee more than the bracket rewarded this year."}}, "Comparative Metrics": {"feature_cols": ["seed_diff", "adj_o_diff", "adj_d_diff", "adj_em_diff", "barthag_diff", "wab_diff", "coach_appearances_diff", "coach_tourn_wins_diff", "coach_final_fours_diff", "coach_win_rate_diff"], "importances": [{"feature": "adj_em_diff", "importance": 0.5165769228460535}, {"feature": "barthag_diff", "importance": 0.09525146076470023}, {"feature": "wab_diff", "importance": 0.08369207485172216}, {"feature": "seed_diff", "importance": 0.07526334824864193}, {"feature": "adj_o_diff", "importance": 0.07114925640997652}, {"feature": "adj_d_diff", "importance": 0.05678349461680831}, {"feature": "coach_win_rate_diff", "importance": 0.043489482622223796}, {"feature": "coach_tourn_wins_diff", "importance": 0.025693873347412105}, {"feature": "coach_appearances_diff", "importance": 0.02334718299596284}, {"feature": "coach_final_fours_diff", "importance": 0.008752903296498606}], "method": "gradient-boosting gain on score-margin (normalized)", "narrative": {"headline": "Comparative Metrics picks the better team, full stop", "body": "Over half of this model's weight goes to a single number: <strong>adj_em_diff</strong> (adjusted efficiency margin). It's asking one question: which team has been flat-out better per possession all season? Seed, coach tenure, and schedule quality get cameo roles. In basketball terms, it's the Ken Pomeroy / Barttorvik view: don't overthink it, pick the team with the bigger scoring gap. Respectable against the field, but notice: where Hindsight sees nuance (seed_disagreement, tempo), this model sees one big blunt instrument."}}, "Lean GB": {"feature_cols": ["barthag_diff", "adj_em_diff", "seed_disagreement", "ast_rate_diff", "min_seed", "is_big_gap", "wab_diff"], "importances": [{"feature": "adj_em_diff", "importance": 0.2856064023104629}, {"feature": "seed_disagreement", "importance": 0.27117939165138477}, {"feature": "ast_rate_diff", "importance": 0.14019955357236225}, {"feature": "wab_diff", "importance": 0.11747171506623201}, {"feature": "barthag_diff", "importance": 0.10589297562046535}, {"feature": "min_seed", "importance": 0.06948023732886106}, {"feature": "is_big_gap", "importance": 0.010169724450231543}], "method": "gradient-boosting gain on win classifier (normalized)", "narrative": {"headline": "Lean GB hunts for mispriced teams", "body": "The lean gradient-boosted classifier's top feature is <strong>seed_disagreement</strong> \u2014 the same one Hindsight says this tournament rewarded. In basketball terms: Lean GB is looking for teams the committee got wrong. A 5-seed whose efficiency numbers belong to a 2-seed is a green light; a 2-seed whose numbers look like a 6-seed is a trap. It's a contrarian approach \u2014 find value where the bracket structure and underlying stats disagree. The Monte Carlo Consensus and Tiered Threshold variants run this same classifier through different bracket strategies (stochastic draw, thresholded picks, 10k-sim majority)."}}}, "pretournament_feature_order": ["con_adj_oe_diff", "con_adj_de_diff", "adj_em_diff", "seed_diff", "wab_diff", "b_adj_em", "conf_winpct_diff", "sos_diff", "a_adj_em", "qual_games_diff", "adj_o_diff", "qual_barthag_diff", "is_late_round", "seed_product", "qual_o_diff", "coach_tourn_wins_diff", "adj_d_diff", "ncsos_diff", "a_adj_o", "seed_sum", "consos_diff", "b_adj_o", "qual_d_diff", "b_barthag", "coach_appearances_diff", "elite_sos_diff", "a_adj_d", "coach_final_fours_diff"]}